The stability of the catalyst is also an important aspect compared to good photoreduction activity. Cyclic experiments of Cr(VI) reduction and Cr(VI)-RBY treatment were performed under the same conditions to evaluate the stability of 8 wt% QDs/N-BM. After five repeated experiments, the photoreducing activity of 8 wt% QDs/N-BM slightly decreased (Fig. 4
                        ). Furthermore, the removal efficiency of the mixed pollutants (Fig. 4b) are more stable than that of single Cr(VI) pollutant (Fig. 4a). Considering that some Cr(III) would adhere to the surface, and the experimental results were within an acceptable range. In addition, the XRD diffraction peaks of the reused samples did not show any significant difference compared to the fresh samples (Fig. 5
                        ). In general, the stability of the material is satisfactory.
